{"title":"Tunisia Diaries: This is the route I took to cycle from London to Tunisia","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/london-to-tunisia-cycling-route","date":1688724310000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/london-to-tunisia-cycling-route\">Tunisia Diaries: This is the route I took to cycle from London to Tunisia</a></p>\n\n<p>I recently completed a bikepacking trip from from London to Tunisia, taking in England, France, Belgium, a swig of Germany, Switzerland and Italy, and this is the route I rode. I might be biased, but it’s absolutely spectacular.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It includes the phenomenal <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/gotthard-pass-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">Gotthard Pass</a> in Switzerland, the magical region of Ticino and crossing the absolutely beautiful Italian Apennines among many other delightful places. It was truly the trip of a lifetime, and what made it <em>even </em>better was the fact I got zero punctures. Glorious.</p>\n\n\n\n<div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>How I planned my route</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-8-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"tuscan hill vista\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-8-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-8-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-8-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-8-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-8-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-8-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-8-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-8-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-8.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Draw a straight line south from London to Tunisia and you pretty much get the idea for my route. I primarily used Komoot and aimed to follow cycle routes wherever possible.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That said, there were many deviations, particularly in France where they seemed to rip roads up left, right and centre, and in Italy where a landslide meant I had to hike my bike up a lot of stairs.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-6-970x646.jpg\" alt=\"cyclist dancing in square\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-6-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-6-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-6-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-6-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-6-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-6-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-6.jpg 1484w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There were also some detours to find boulangeries, supermarkets, and campsites, plus when I cycled with people and they were taking the route round the hill rather than over the top I couldn’t help but join them.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While I did plan my route roughly before I started riding, I usually did the majority of decision making the night before or on the day as I liked the spontaneity.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikepacking-tips\">Tunisia Diaries: 7 things I wish I had known before I set off on my bikepacking adventure</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikepacking-clothes\">Tunisia Diaries: How many clothes is too many for a bikepacking trip?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/bikepacking-guide-how-to-pack-your-bike-and-yourself\">Bikepacking guide: How to pack your bike, and yourself</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Choice of ferries</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"728\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-2-970x728.jpg\" alt=\"tunisian ferry\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-2-970x728.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-2-300x225.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-2-768x576.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-2-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-2-750x563.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-2-1140x855.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-2.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I decided to get the ferry from Dover to Calais because I had never ridden from London to Dover, whereas I had done London to Brighton. Simple as.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The decision to take the ferry from Civitavecchia in Italy came about because all the other ferries were booked up from Salerno (near Naples). I discovered that very last minute (I’m not a huge planner), so my last day was pretty much a race to catch the only ferry available for a week or so. The ferry from Civitavecchia to Tunis was unglamorous but perfectly fine. It took 18 hours and I slept on the floor.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Route highlights</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Day 5: A glorious gravel track</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-5-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"gravel road\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-5-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-5-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-5-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-5-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-5-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-5-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-5-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-5-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-5.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I headed out of Saint-Mihiel towards Commercy. A very steep hill morphed into a gravel track that kept going up until it revealed its summit. Always worth it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Day 10: The Gotthard pass</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-gotthard-14-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"cyclist gotthard pass\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-gotthard-14-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-gotthard-14-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-gotthard-14-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-gotthard-14-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-gotthard-14-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-gotthard-14-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-gotthard-14-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-gotthard-14-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-gotthard-14-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-gotthard-14.jpg 1800w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I feel like the name says it all. Conquering a mountain pass with 20kg of bikepacking luggage was always going to be a challenge, but completing it was one of the best feelings in the world.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Day 11: Cycling through Ticino</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-5-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"cyclist looking back on hill\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-5-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-5-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-5-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-5-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-5-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-5-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-5-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-stuff-5.jpg 1024w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Following a mixture of Eurovelo 3 and 311 I headed over cobbled streets, back roads, up the Monte Ceneri hairpins, descended through vineyards near Coldrerio and pedalled around Il Lago di Lugano. It was utterly beautiful. I think my mouth was open most of the day.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Day 15: The Apennines</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-9-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"lovely view\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-9-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-9-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-9-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-9-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-9-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-9-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-9-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-9-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-9.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Heading into Tuscany over the Apennines was a truly majestic road that follows the Eurovelo 7 (the sun route). My favourite part was from Il Lago di Suviana down to Montemurlo, which had insane switchbacks nestled in what felt like a rainforest. It was quite remote, the road was smooth and I climbed up to the most amazing view.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I was then treated to a spectacular, albeit potholed descent down to Montemurlo, which links up to Prato.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The route</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-9-970x647.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-9-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-9-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-9-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-9-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-9-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-9-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-9-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-9-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/emma-tunisia-day1-3-recap-9.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The route is both tarmac and gravel, as well as a few bits of grass and cobbles thrown in along the way, especially in Belgium and Italy. Oh, and there is one small stream crossing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is best suited to a gravel bike – I chose the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/ribble-gravel-ti\" target=\"_blank\">Ribble Gravel Ti Hero.</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Would I do anything differently?</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-10-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"vineyards\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-10-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-10-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-10-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-10-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-10-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-10-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-10-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-10-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-10-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/emma-tunisia-route-10.jpg 1600w\" /><figcaption>Emma Cole</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There was one less exciting day heading from Parma to Bologna. It was mostly on a straight main road, which made things quite boring and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/motivation-on-long-rides\" target=\"_blank\">challenging mentally</a>. I would change this to weave in and out of the farmland and take some other detours. Basically, anything other than staying on the same straight road with traffic whizzing past. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But overall? It was a pretty marvellous route.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Want to know more about Emma’s ride from London to Tunisia? Here’s <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikepacking-kit-list\" target=\"_blank\">what she packed</a>, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bikepacking-tips\" target=\"_blank\">7 things she wish she had known before she set off</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/ribble-gravel-ti\" target=\"_blank\">the bike she rode</a>. </em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/london-to-tunisia-cycling-route\">Tunisia Diaries: This is the route I took to cycle from London to Tunisia</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Emma Cole &#124; Features Writer","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"da56769c0953876dbc85cc68df2e5fda632e309ee3c01822f7fca230491b6f7a","category":"Cycling"}